Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.52,0:00:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.40,0:00:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good afternoon everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.10,0:00:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to WWDC2017.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.94,0:00:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is David Duncan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.21,0:00:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be joined by Raj Ramamurphy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.54,0:00:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[phonetic] and Kyle Sluder
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.63,0:00:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[phonetic].
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're here to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.81,0:00:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,about updating your app for iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.02,0:00:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.18,0:00:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So first a little agenda for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.08,0:00:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.42,0:00:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.82,0:00:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing that I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.97,0:00:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to be discussing with you is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.37,0:00:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,adopting new functionality in UI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.49,0:00:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,kits bars; UI navigation bar, UI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.59,0:00:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,tab bar, UI toolbar, and UI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.43,0:00:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,search bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.09,0:01:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,about how these can update your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.22,0:01:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,app to the new looks that we've
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.14,0:01:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced throughout iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.27,0:01:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Next Kyle will come up and talk
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.96,0:01:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to you a bit about managing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.12,0:01:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,margins and insets, changes that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.12,0:01:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we've made to UI scroll view and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.66,0:01:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,table view will come after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.82,0:01:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're going to use all that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.29,0:01:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to show you how you can make
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.19,0:01:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your app better.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.26,0:01:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's start by taking a look
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.09,0:01:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,at the files app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.62,0:01:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you've gotten the chance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.90,0:01:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to install the beta and take a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.62,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the files app, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.18,0:01:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,see some changes that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.59,0:01:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,taking advantage of from UI kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.13,0:01:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that giant, large
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.64,0:01:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,title view up there showing the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.13,0:01:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,browse feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.93,0:01:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a search bar right
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.99,0:01:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,below it that has a bit of a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.25,0:01:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,different appearance from any
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.49,0:01:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,search bar you've probably seen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.60,0:01:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.21,0:01:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the tab bar actually has
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.27,0:01:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,some changes, but you won't see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.07,0:01:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,them here so let's go ahead and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.47,0:01:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,rotate this to landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.14,0:01:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got this brand new
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.50,0:02:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance for the tab bar, both
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.42,0:02:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in landscape and on iPad, where
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.88,0:02:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we show the icon and the text
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.56,0:02:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,side by side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.32,0:02:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And in particular on iPhones the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,icon is smaller and the tab bar
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.11,0:02:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is smaller to give a bit more
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.37,0:02:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,room vertically.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.71,0:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to discuss how you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,can customize the icons for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.64,0:02:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape and tab bar as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.07,0:02:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now things getting smaller can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.80,0:02:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes be a problem for users
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that are hard of vision or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise need a little
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.18,0:02:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,assistance to see things
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.17,0:02:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,clearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.55,0:02:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got you covered there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you turn on larger text then
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.12,0:02:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,when you long press on one of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.16,0:02:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these items -- this is in tab
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.00,0:02:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,bar, tool bar, and navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.36,0:02:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,bar -- we'll put up this HUD
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.61,0:02:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that shows you clearly what the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.03,0:02:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,text is and what the icon is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.21,0:02:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'm going to explain how
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.59,0:02:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,both of these features can be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.81,0:02:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,adopted in your app and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.07,0:02:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,really, really easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's this class called UI
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.13,0:02:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Bar Item that you probably never
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.89,0:02:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,thought much about because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.22,0:03:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the super class of two
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.41,0:03:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,important bar item classes in UI
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,kit; UI tab bar item and UI bar
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,button item.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.76,0:03:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so to customize the image in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.29,0:03:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape on that tab bar all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.77,0:03:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to do is set this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.95,0:03:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,property, the landscape image
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,phone property, on any UI tab
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.24,0:03:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,bar items that you're placing in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.91,0:03:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your tab bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.66,0:03:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we'll have support
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.45,0:03:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for this in storyboards and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.46,0:03:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,everywhere else, but that's how
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you would customize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.10,0:03:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are also some inset
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.13,0:03:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,properties in case you need
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.26,0:03:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,those.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For that HUD image we've got
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.88,0:03:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,another related property called
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.44,0:03:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the Large Content Size Image.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.75,0:03:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can set this, put a big
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,image in there, it'll appear in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.19,0:03:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the HUD, but if you're using PDF
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.73,0:03:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,assets in your asset catalogue
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's even easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.97,0:03:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is set that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.79,0:03:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,preserve PDF data and we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.16,0:03:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically pick up the PDF
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.57,0:03:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,data, resize it larger, and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:03:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,display it in that HUD without
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.41,0:03:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you having to do anything to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.52,0:03:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.09,0:04:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you wanted to learn more
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.43,0:04:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about accessibility features
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the HUD and how you can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.98,0:04:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,pick that up, there's the What's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,New in Accessibility session
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,happening this Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.95,0:04:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend you go there to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.36,0:04:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,learn all about what's new in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.39,0:04:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.02,0:04:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And so let's talk next about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.89,0:04:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we get those large titles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that appeared in the files app
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.30,0:04:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and other apps across the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.29,0:04:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,system?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So first there's a new property
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.97,0:04:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on UI navigation bar, prefers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.44,0:04:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,large titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you set this to "true" on any
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.57,0:04:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,given navigation bar then you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,start seeing large titles all
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.49,0:04:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,across the system -- all across
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.49,0:04:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.36,0:04:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you might be wondering; what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,do these other three words that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.33,0:04:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got here on this slide --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.56,0:04:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe they're a little hard to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.48,0:04:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,see, but automatic, always, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.03,0:04:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,never -- what does that have to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,do with?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.95,0:04:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's a second property
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.78,0:04:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to control when these appear;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.00,0:04:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the large title display mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.89,0:04:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what easily allows you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.35,0:04:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to determine for each view
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.55,0:04:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,control you push onto a nav
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.89,0:05:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,controller or to a navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.13,0:05:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,bar stack when the large title
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.44,0:05:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And let me show you how that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,works.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.33,0:05:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we turned on large titles on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.05,0:05:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this navigation bar and we put
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.29,0:05:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,an item on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.46,0:05:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It defaults to automatic and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.35,0:05:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic means whatever the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.46,0:05:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,current state is, whoever asked
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.51,0:05:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,last for that bar to appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.78,0:05:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.05,0:05:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Since nothing else is on the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.33,0:05:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,stack and we turned on large
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,titles, we have a large title.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.23,0:05:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's go ahead and push a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.23,0:05:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation item that we don't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.52,0:05:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,want to display that large title
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.90,0:05:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on and we just set the large
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.00,0:05:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,title display mode to "never"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.33,0:05:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the large title goes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.08,0:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now again we'll push an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"automatic," preserve whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.51,0:05:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we have now, and so we don't get
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.13,0:05:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a large title, and then we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.93,0:05:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,push "always," and now the large
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.29,0:05:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,title is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, we can push an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.55,0:05:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"automatic" and we're all there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple. So there are two more
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.27,0:05:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,things we want to talk about on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.74,0:05:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation item and the first is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,how to integrate the search
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.23,0:06:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,controller and the new search
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.49,0:06:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,bar look with your navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.46,0:06:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a single property again,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.56,0:06:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation item search
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.73,0:06:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.72,0:06:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You assign your search
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.48,0:06:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,controller to the navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.53,0:06:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,item and you're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.59,0:06:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The search bar is placed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly and it behaves just as
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.33,0:06:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it does in a lot of our apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.62,0:06:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you've actually gotten a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.64,0:06:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,chance to play with "files" or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.49,0:06:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"mail" or some of the others
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.70,0:06:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice that sometimes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.94,0:06:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that search bar stays pegged
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when you scroll, sometimes it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.44,0:06:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.27,0:06:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular in "files" it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,stays pegged and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.22,0:06:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,controlled by this "hide search
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.39,0:06:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,bar when scrolling" property.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.13,0:06:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It defaults to "true."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.28,0:06:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example in "mail" it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.69,0:06:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolls away, but in "files"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,they've turned it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.94,0:06:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it stays pegged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.35,0:06:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can always reach the search
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.40,0:06:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,bar and it looks great.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.36,0:06:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does all this work?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A little bit of behind the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.11,0:06:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,scenes on some of these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first thing you should
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,know is that a lot of these
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:06:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,interactions are actually
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:06:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,mediated by UI navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.63,0:06:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.57,0:07:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're taking the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.23,0:07:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bar and assembling
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.07,0:07:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of the entire push and pop
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.35,0:07:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,experience yourself, and not
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.75,0:07:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,many people do, but if you are
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.94,0:07:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to get some of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,these features.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.01,0:07:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular you're not going
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.64,0:07:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the search controller
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.58,0:07:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,integration.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to get refresh
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.54,0:07:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,controls hoisting and you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.64,0:07:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,going to get rubber bending.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.59,0:07:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Rubber bending is when you start
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.96,0:07:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,pulling down, that large title
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.46,0:07:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,grows larger, and responds to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that scroller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.67,0:07:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's navigation bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.61,0:07:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation controller, and those
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.39,0:07:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,new large title features.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.85,0:07:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But while we're here making all
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of these changes we figured
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.83,0:07:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,let's actually make some other
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.02,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,changes to help your lives be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.46,0:07:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,easier as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so now in iOS 11, UI toolbar
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.76,0:07:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and UI navigation bar both have
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.85,0:07:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,intricate and express support
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.60,0:07:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for auto layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.52,0:07:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.61,0:07:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So what this means is that your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.27,0:07:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,custom bar button items, your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.71,0:07:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,custom title of use, can now use
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.22,0:08:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,layout to express their size to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.13,0:08:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,us and get the proper layout
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.28,0:08:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would otherwise expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.33,0:08:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there are a few things to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.73,0:08:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,keep in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.93,0:08:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them is you kind of want
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.97,0:08:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep your constraints inside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.22,0:08:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of that view.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.29,0:08:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you give us a custom title
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,view you want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.50,0:08:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,any constraints there only
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.36,0:08:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,reference that title view and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.95,0:08:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,any of its sub-views.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.76,0:08:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one is kind of big, but
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.78,0:08:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's kind of worth bringing out,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is that when you use auto layout
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.14,0:08:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we also assume you know what
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.22,0:08:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing [laughter] and the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.75,0:08:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,reason why I bring this up is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,because otherwise you end up in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.87,0:08:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,this case where you have to --
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.89,0:08:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you get zero sized views.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do you avoid these zero
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.16,0:08:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sized views?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, UI navigation bar and UI
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.16,0:08:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,toolbar provide positioning
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.32,0:08:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.80,0:08:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero sized views end up becoming
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.37,0:08:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because you have some ambiguous
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the position is taken
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.25,0:08:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,care of for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.89,0:08:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't get your views shoved
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.95,0:08:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,up in an upper left corner
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.09,0:08:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere, but you still have to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.37,0:08:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,provide sizing for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.95,0:08:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are three ways you can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You could add constraints for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.10,0:09:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,width and height; perfectly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.38,0:09:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,legal, perfectly legitimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.76,0:09:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do that. You can put whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.54,0:09:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,else you want in there and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.97,0:09:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you're golden.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.08,0:09:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You could also implement
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.45,0:09:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsic content size.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.82,0:09:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll also give us as much
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.63,0:09:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,information as we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.38,0:09:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You go along with the content
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.45,0:09:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,compression hugging and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.34,0:09:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,compression resistance and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.59,0:09:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you're set.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.74,0:09:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But finally, the most easy way,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.57,0:09:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for most people, is to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.57,0:09:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that all of your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.59,0:09:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,sub-views are properly connected
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and set up with auto layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.49,0:09:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And what that means is let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.83,0:09:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a custom title view and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.02,0:09:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a label and a button in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.28,0:09:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,there, if you want to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.42,0:09:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that you get the proper
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.73,0:09:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,horizontal width of that title
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,view you just need to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.56,0:09:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are constraints set
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.43,0:09:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,up between those labels and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.72,0:09:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons such that the leading
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.15,0:09:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and trailing edge, or the width,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.25,0:09:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of that title view is defined in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,terms of those two views.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.28,0:09:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that's how you can use
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.33,0:09:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,auto layout to add precise
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.01,0:10:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,control to the size of your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.71,0:10:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,custom title views and bar
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.01,0:10:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,button items.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.44,0:10:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to demonstrate all the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,things we've talked about today
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.66,0:10:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we bring up Raj Ramamurphy to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.60,0:10:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,give you a demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.75,0:10:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks David.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.77,0:10:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So as David just explained, we
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.99,0:10:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have a bunch of great new API in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.06,0:10:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 for these new, large
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.92,0:10:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.35,0:10:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to walk you through
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.33,0:10:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,updating an app for iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.25,0:10:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's a sample app we're
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be working with today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.18,0:10:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pretty simple app called
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.83,0:10:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"Trail Diary."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.04,0:10:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a diary of some trails
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.28,0:10:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I visited.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.64,0:10:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we are in the main view
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, which I called the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.94,0:10:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"memory view controller."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.66,0:10:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if I tap on one of these
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.06,0:10:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,cells you'll notice I get a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.67,0:10:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,detail view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.22,0:10:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This contains a photo, a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,description, and some
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.74,0:10:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,information about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.73,0:10:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also a way to add
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:10:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,comments, and we're going to get
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.05,0:10:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,into that a little bit later,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.49,0:10:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but for now let's start updating
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.28,0:10:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this app for iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.32,0:10:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the first things I'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.62,0:11:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to do is introduce support in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.69,0:11:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,this application for those
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.10,0:11:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful, new large titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go ahead and do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.07,0:11:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go over to the navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.08,0:11:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-- or sorry -- to the memory
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.98,0:11:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller here and we're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.88,0:11:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,going to get the navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.73,0:11:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the navigation bar and set
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.06,0:11:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the "prefers large titles"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.26,0:11:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,property on the navigation bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.00,0:11:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we set this property
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we get large titles everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.92,0:11:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I recompile and rerun the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,application, head back over to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.30,0:11:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it, and bring up the memory view
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.11,0:11:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,controller you'll notice we have
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this beautiful, large title, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.52,0:11:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,since we already have a refresh
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.62,0:11:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,control that gets hoisted into
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.21,0:11:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the navigation bar and we get
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.69,0:11:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the rubber banding experience --
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.13,0:11:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everything's looking great.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.88,0:11:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, "prefers large titles" will
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.39,0:11:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,turn large titles on everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.66,0:11:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I tap back into the detail
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.51,0:11:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller you'll see we
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.95,0:11:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,get a really nice transition and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.55,0:11:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the detail view
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.39,0:11:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,controller showing a large title
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.72,0:12:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.13,0:12:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is great, but sometimes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.66,0:12:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the large title isn't what you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.88,0:12:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,want everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.36,0:12:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so for that, as David
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.97,0:12:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,explained, we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation item property, "large
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.86,0:12:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,title display mode."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.96,0:12:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this view I'd like to show
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.42,0:12:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the standard inline title.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's update this view
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,controller to show that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.25,0:12:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go over to the detail view
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.94,0:12:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,controller and set its
