Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.35,0:12:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,display mode to "never," as
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.51,0:12:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,David showed you before with the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.79,0:12:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,stack, if we recompile and rerun
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the application, we'll start out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.45,0:12:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the large title, but if I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.00,0:12:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,push view controller now we have
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.59,0:12:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this standard inline title and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.22,0:12:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you get a great transition
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.14,0:12:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,between them and everything's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.42,0:12:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,looking really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.33,0:12:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how to use the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.07,0:12:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation item properties for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.25,0:12:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,showing the large title, but I'd
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,also like to add search to this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.81,0:12:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.26,0:12:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've already gone ahead and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,configured a search controller
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.58,0:12:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,instance and I just need to show
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.07,0:12:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the search bar in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.99,0:12:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As you may have seen, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.49,0:13:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,showing search bars in the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.70,0:13:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's add that appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.56,0:13:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go over to the memory view
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,controller again and set the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation item's search
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.40,0:13:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,controller property to our
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.70,0:13:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,instance -- in this case it's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.59,0:13:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,just called "search controller."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Recompile and rerun the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.12,0:13:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice when the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.01,0:13:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,application comes up into the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.23,0:13:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,memory view controller, we still
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have the large title, but now if
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.80,0:13:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we pull down we get this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.24,0:13:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful new search appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.55,0:13:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So this app is looking really
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.82,0:13:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,great.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.77,0:13:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's just how to update
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,some of your bars for the new
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.24,0:13:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.10,0:13:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to bring Kyle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.50,0:13:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sluder up who's going to talk to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.02,0:13:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you about margins, insets, and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.71,0:13:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll views.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.52,0:13:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.17,0:13:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.35,0:13:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you Raj.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.50,0:14:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So in iOS 11 we've made a number
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.16,0:14:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of improvements to give you more
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.55,0:14:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,information and better control
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.40,0:14:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,over how your views lay out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.77,0:14:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,their user interfaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.61,0:14:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's start by talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.81,0:14:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,layout margins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout margins are a portion of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.76,0:14:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the interior of your views that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.19,0:14:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,UI kit gives you as a guide to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.51,0:14:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,layout your content and give a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.67,0:14:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,little breathing room between it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and the surrounding user
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.56,0:14:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,interface elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.99,0:14:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And we give this information to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.12,0:14:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you in two ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.36,0:14:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is a UI layout guide
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.97,0:14:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,object, which you can use with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.74,0:14:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,auto layout to position your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.59,0:14:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.32,0:14:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is a set of edge
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.12,0:14:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,insets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.76,0:14:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can read these from your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.09,0:14:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,view and write to them to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.89,0:14:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,customize your layout margins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.61,0:14:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11 we're adding a new
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.93,0:14:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,property; directional layout
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.66,0:14:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,margins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.79,0:14:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And this allows you to express
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the layout margins in your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.00,0:14:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,views, not just in left and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:14:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,right terms, but in leading and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.18,0:14:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.56,0:14:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And these two properties are in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.30,0:14:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,sync with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.09,0:15:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The left property is in sync
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.68,0:15:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with the leading, when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.57,0:15:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,writing in an LTR or left to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.11,0:15:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,right language.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.53,0:15:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the right property and the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.53,0:15:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing property are in sync.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.36,0:15:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can do something like write
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.11,0:15:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a value to the trailing property
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of this view, which will cause
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.46,0:15:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,its layout to adjust, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.06,0:15:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when I'm running in a right to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.90,0:15:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,left language that trailing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,space will be put on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,side of the view and my layout
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.58,0:15:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,code can then read it from the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.95,0:15:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,left property of the layout
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.71,0:15:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,margin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.52,0:15:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.05,0:15:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You may also be familiar with a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.05,0:15:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior that has existed since
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.34,0:15:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we introduced layout margins
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,where adding a view to a view
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.30,0:15:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,controller would fix its layout
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.20,0:15:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,margins to UI kit defined
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.09,0:15:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,values.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.52,0:15:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well starting in iOS 11 these
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.60,0:15:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are no longer fixed values.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They're actually minimums.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we communicate the size of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.78,0:15:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,these values to you with this
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.28,0:15:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,new property, system minimum
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.11,0:15:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,layout margins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can change your view's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.81,0:15:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,layout margins to any greater
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.62,0:15:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,value, no changes needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.52,0:16:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But we went one step further and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we added another new property on
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.83,0:16:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller; view respects
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.50,0:16:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,system minimum layout margins.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.46,0:16:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you set this to "false" you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.09,0:16:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,can actually change your layout
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.16,0:16:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,margins to whatever value you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.28,0:16:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,want, including zero, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,can have full width content in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.55,0:16:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,any view including those that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.26,0:16:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,are managed by a view
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.93,0:16:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.26,0:16:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Since iOS 7 we've had these
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.26,0:16:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,translucent bars throughout the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,operating system and we've
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.75,0:16:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,encouraged you to draw your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,content through those bars, as
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.49,0:16:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see happening here in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.40,0:16:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the photos app.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.15,0:16:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The way that you do this is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.21,0:16:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,using the edges for extended
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.60,0:16:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,layout property on UI view
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.02,0:16:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.10,0:16:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And what this does is it causes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.33,0:16:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,container view controllers to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,size your views underneath the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.68,0:16:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.03,0:16:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,By default it applies to all
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.02,0:16:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,edges and we communicate to you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.44,0:16:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the size of the overhanging bars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.62,0:16:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,via these two properties; top
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.18,0:16:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,layout guide and bottom layout
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.56,0:16:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.99,0:17:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in iOS 11 we're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.18,0:17:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,deprecating these properties and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.92,0:17:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,replacing them with a new, more
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.84,0:17:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful construct that we call
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.40,0:17:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the "safe area."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.22,0:17:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The safe area is a way of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,describing the portion of your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.23,0:17:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,view that isn't occluded by any
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.91,0:17:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.28,0:17:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's available to you as a set
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.83,0:17:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of insets or as a UI layout
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.70,0:17:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,guide object.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.19,0:17:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And on TV it incorporates a very
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.12,0:17:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,useful bit of information called
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.87,0:17:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the "over scan compensation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.23,0:17:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,insets."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.06,0:17:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So any view on the screen can
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.74,0:17:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,layout its content and make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.61,0:17:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that it isn't overlapped by the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.84,0:17:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,physical bezel of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.13,0:17:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,television.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.18,0:17:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you have a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,container view controller, you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.73,0:17:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,might be adding your own bars
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.49,0:17:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can increase the size of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.85,0:17:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the -- excuse me -- you can
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.10,0:17:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,increase the size of the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.92,0:17:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,area insets via this new
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.10,0:17:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,property; additional safe area
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,insets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And if any of your ancestor view
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.62,0:17:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,controllers change their size of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.40,0:17:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,their safe area insets you will
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.42,0:17:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,get a call back in two different
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.67,0:17:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.28,0:18:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Every view can get safe area
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.07,0:18:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,insets to change and view
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.57,0:18:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,controllers can get view safe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.91,0:18:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,area insets to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.90,0:18:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[applause] Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.46,0:18:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So one really common view that's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.58,0:18:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,used with UI view controller is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.09,0:18:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,UI scroll view.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this little sample here I
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.03,0:18:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,have some text that's inside of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.29,0:18:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI scroll view and contained
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.93,0:18:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,within a navigation controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.77,0:18:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now traditionally navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.39,0:18:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,controllers would impart a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.71,0:18:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,content inset to the scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.81,0:18:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,views of their topmost view
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.30,0:18:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're making a really big change
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.16,0:18:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,here in iOS 11 and we're no
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.89,0:18:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,longer populating the content
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,inset property through scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.60,0:18:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,views.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.39,0:18:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead we've added a new
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.36,0:18:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,property, adjusted content
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.18,0:18:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,inset, that includes the sum of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.54,0:18:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the content inset and any
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,overlap from container view
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.10,0:18:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,controllers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.88,0:18:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This means you can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.38,0:18:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,content inset property for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.86,0:18:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever purposes are
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.20,0:18:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate for your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.89,0:18:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,application, such as this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.42,0:18:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,additional information about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this text here, and we won't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.98,0:19:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to worry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.89,0:19:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about saving and restoring any
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.27,0:19:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,UI kit provided values and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,having content underlapping
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.49,0:19:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bars or the status
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.82,0:19:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.55,0:19:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be familiar with our
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.99,0:19:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,auto layout support in UI scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.47,0:19:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,view that lets you dictate how
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.44,0:19:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,big the scrollable region of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.81,0:19:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,your scroll view is by
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.29,0:19:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,constraining sub-views to the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll view itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.18,0:19:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've added a couple of UI
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,layout guide objects that make
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.14,0:19:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,your layout more clear and more
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.03,0:19:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,expressive and more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.99,0:19:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is a UI layout guide
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.76,0:19:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,object called the frame layout
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.10,0:19:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And this layout guide
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.27,0:19:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,corresponds to the position and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.10,0:19:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,size of your scroll view in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.49,0:19:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,screen space, which means you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.64,0:19:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can do things like constrain the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.98,0:19:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,sub-view, like this page
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.13,0:19:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator, and it will stay
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,fixed on screen as the user
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.02,0:19:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.97,0:19:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The second layout guide object
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.22,0:19:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we've added is the content
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.68,0:19:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,layout guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.77,0:19:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can contain your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.79,0:19:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,sub-views in order to influence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.15,0:19:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the scrollable size of your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.66,0:20:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll view or have things move
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.30,0:20:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as the user scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.92,0:20:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,One really common sub class of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.81,0:20:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,UI scroll view is UI table view
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.07,0:20:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've made a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.90,0:20:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,changes here too, the biggest of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.47,0:20:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,which is that table views use
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.45,0:20:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,self-sizing by default on iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,11, not on TVOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.12,0:20:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that your headers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.45,0:20:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your footers, and your cells are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.56,0:20:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,using estimated sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.99,0:20:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done this by changing the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.07,0:20:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,default value of the estimated
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.08,0:20:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,size properties on UI table view
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.25,0:20:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to this constant, automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.46,0:20:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.92,0:20:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,ensure that your cells all have
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.74,0:20:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,sufficient internal constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.17,0:20:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell UI table view how big
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they should be or you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.30,0:20:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,implement the delegate methods
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.96,0:20:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that tell us how big your rows
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.36,0:20:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.78,0:20:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You should also implement those
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.85,0:20:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,delicate methods for you headers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.71,0:20:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and your footers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.83,0:20:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now maybe you want to link your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.29,0:20:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,application against the iOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.88,0:20:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,SDK, but you're not ready to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,adopt this new behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.52,0:20:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can opt out of it by setting
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.03,0:21:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the estimated height properties
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.43,0:21:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on your table views to zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.48,0:21:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That will turn off estimated
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.93,0:21:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes, which will also disable
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.24,0:21:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,self-sizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you may be familiar with
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.10,0:21:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,another concept we introduced a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.23,0:21:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,while back called the readable
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,content guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.94,0:21:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a portion of your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.11,0:21:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,views that if you lay out your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,content within, will be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.81,0:21:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortable to read even on a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.06,0:21:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,large device like an iPad in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.93,0:21:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now by default table views have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a separator inset that is within
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.11,0:21:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the readable content area and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.15,0:21:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this influences the position of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.45,0:21:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the separators and of the labels
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the table use content view
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.80,0:21:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.32,0:21:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you change the separator
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.06,0:21:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,insets' values you would see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.77,0:21:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that the separator inset moves
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.59,0:21:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,relative to its readable content
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.60,0:21:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,guide position.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.07,0:21:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in iOS 11 we're
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.35,0:21:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,changing this and the separator
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.44,0:21:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,insets will always be relative
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.28,0:21:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to the edges of the cells
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.37,0:21:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves, which are the full
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.57,0:21:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,width of the table view, which
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:21:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,means you can set these values
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.53,0:22:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to zero and have full width,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.78,0:22:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,full bleed content even on an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.60,0:22:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad running in landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.30,0:22:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a table view on an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.01,0:22:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone and if I change the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.73,0:22:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,separator inset here you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.98,0:22:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is also defined relative
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.74,0:22:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the edges of the cell -- to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.32,0:22:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the edge of the table view.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.28,0:22:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We've added a new property to UI
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.42,0:22:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,table view, separator inset
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.89,0:22:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reference, that you can use to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.24,0:22:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,tell us that you actually just
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.43,0:22:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,want to adjust the separator
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.04,0:22:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,inset from its default automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.83,0:22:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,position.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.18,0:22:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this works on iPad too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.85,0:22:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of things to keep in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.02,0:22:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,mind about the way the table
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.95,0:22:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,views interact with the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.06,0:22:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,area; those automatic separator
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.04,0:22:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,insets are relative to the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.65,0:22:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,area insets.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.73,0:22:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So by default the entire content
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.48,0:22:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of your table view avoids the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.03,0:22:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,safe area insets from its
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.38,0:22:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ancestor view controllers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,UI table view cell and UI table
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,view header/footer view, which
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.97,0:22:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,might be one of the longer names
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.08,0:22:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in the kit, they both have a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.94,0:22:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,content view property.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.45,0:22:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you should be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.26,0:22:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,adding your sub-views.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.28,0:22:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of these classes make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.64,0:23:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that that content view also
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.53,0:23:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,avoids the safe area insets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.65,0:23:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you should be using UI table
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.21,0:23:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,view header/footer view for all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.18,0:23:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the headers and footers in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.16,0:23:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,your table views; table headers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.90,0:23:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and footers and section headers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.24,0:23:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and footers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.35,0:23:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also brought over the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.50,0:23:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,really rich swipe action
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.99,0:23:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality from the mail
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.59,0:23:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,application to your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.78,0:23:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.15,0:23:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So on iOS 11 your applications
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.18,0:23:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,will get the new swipe action
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.43,0:23:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,look and feel by default, and if
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.60,0:23:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you link against iOS 11, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.26,0:23:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,get full swipe to delete
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.64,0:23:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior, just like you're used
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.99,0:23:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to from the mail app.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.60,0:23:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go ahead --
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.97,0:23:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[applause] some people are very
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.62,0:23:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,excited about this I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.41,0:23:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[applause] And if you go ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.84,0:23:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and adopt a few new APIs you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.74,0:23:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,get some really cool features,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.39,0:23:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,like images in your swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.74,0:23:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,actions, or swipe actions from
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.74,0:23:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,both the leading and the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.88,0:23:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing edges, or a completion
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.65,0:23:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,handler that lets you cancel the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.94,0:23:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,swipe action.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.07,0:23:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And to show us how to adopt all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.29,0:23:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,these features in our
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.89,0:23:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,application, Raj is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.24,0:23:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,come up and give us another
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.93,0:23:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.41,0:23:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Raj?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.52,0:24:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.41,0:24:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.60,0:24:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to switch over to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.58,0:24:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the demo machine again and as
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.51,0:24:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see we've got these big
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.14,0:24:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful bars in this new
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.29,0:24:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.29,0:24:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's looking really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.44,0:24:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want to show you the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.12,0:24:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,comments view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.11,0:24:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if I push into the comments
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.65,0:24:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller here, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.22,0:24:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,notice we have some really
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.27,0:24:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting comments and we've
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.64,0:24:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,got all the comments here in a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.05,0:24:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,comment bar at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.10,0:24:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now our users have been asking
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.59,0:24:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,us for one thing and that's time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.47,0:24:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,stamps.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.44,0:24:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I went and spoke to our
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.78,0:24:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,designer and got this really
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.37,0:24:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,cool design for this awesome new
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.09,0:24:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.44,0:24:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This scroll bar also indicates,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.86,0:24:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,not only where you are in the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.51,0:24:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,comments view, but also the time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.45,0:24:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,stamp where it's pointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.67,0:24:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go ahead and implement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.15,0:24:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.46,0:24:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll switch over to the comments
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.61,0:24:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller and create our
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.46,0:24:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll bar using a method I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.43,0:24:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.88,0:24:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I recompile and rerun
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.18,0:25:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the application, scroll down,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.31,0:25:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,tap on one of these cells, and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.66,0:25:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,into the comments view
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.35,0:25:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,controller you'll see there it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.57,0:25:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.64,0:25:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's looking pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.78,0:25:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows you where you are in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.12,0:25:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,this comments view controller
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.82,0:25:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the time stamp of the cell
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.53,0:25:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's pointing at.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.15,0:25:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But, as you might notice, there
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.78,0:25:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,are a few issues here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.24,0:25:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The first issue is that this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.91,0:25:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator actually overlaps with
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.72,0:25:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the table view cell a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.31,0:25:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and so it makes things maybe a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.47,0:25:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit hard to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.29,0:25:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The second thing is that this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.94,0:25:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator overlaps with this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.15,0:25:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,input field here at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.38,0:25:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's use some new APIs in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.47,0:25:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 to help solve these
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.86,0:25:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.92,0:25:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to use the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.60,0:25:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,additional safe area insets
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.15,0:25:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,property on UI view controller
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.59,0:25:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to help solve this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.41,0:25:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll go ahead and unwrap our
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.77,0:25:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,two views and I'll set our
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.96,0:25:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,additional safe area insets to a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.58,0:25:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,UA edge insets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.37,0:25:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So on the top we don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.07,0:25:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,anything additional to add.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.00,0:25:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,On the left that's the same
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.38,0:25:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,story.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.35,0:26:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,On the bottom we want to make it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.98,0:26:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the comment bar's size.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.37,0:26:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll get the height of the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.46,0:26:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,comment bar and on the right we
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.73,0:26:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,have a property that I've
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.64,0:26:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,written earlier on the side
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.29,0:26:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator that gives its
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.52,0:26:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,preferred width.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.62,0:26:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we've set up our
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.11,0:26:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,additional safe area insets.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.98,0:26:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If I recompile and rerun the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.68,0:26:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,application, head into the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.85,0:26:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,detail view and again into the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.32,0:26:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,comments view controller, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.81,0:26:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,notice things are starting to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.90,0:26:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,look pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.37,0:26:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got our content inset from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.18,0:26:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the right edge and the scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.66,0:26:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator's also inset from the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.15,0:26:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom edge, but you'll notice
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.42,0:26:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,here, down at the bottom, that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.93,0:26:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,this comment field actually is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.61,0:26:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,inset a little bit from the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.73,0:26:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,right edge of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.80,0:26:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reason for that is the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.53,0:26:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,comment field's text field is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.31,0:26:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,constrained to its super views
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.11,0:26:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,layout margins.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.84,0:26:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in iOS 11 your layout
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.08,0:26:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,margins are actually inset from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.05,0:27:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the safe area and because we
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.29,0:27:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,added additional safe area
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.69,0:27:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,insets on the right of this view
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.99,0:27:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,our layout margins get inset
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.32,0:27:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.84,0:27:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now most of the time this is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.21,0:27:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be exactly what you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.38,0:27:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,want, but we do have a property
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.48,0:27:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,on UI view, "insets layout
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.74,0:27:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,margins from safe area," which
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.75,0:27:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,lets you control this property.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.59,0:27:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So for this use case let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.24,0:27:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead and set that to "false."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.05,0:27:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When I go ahead and do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.53,0:27:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,recompile and rerun the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.17,0:27:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,application, go back into the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.91,0:27:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,detail view controller and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.26,0:27:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,finally into the comments view
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.19,0:27:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, you'll see things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.06,0:27:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,are starting to look really
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.90,0:27:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.65,0:27:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got our content at the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.92,0:27:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,right spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.97,0:27:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got our beautiful new
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.84,0:27:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll indicator.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.04,0:27:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is inset and the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.90,0:27:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,comment field is a full width.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.75,0:27:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome! The next thing I'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.82,0:27:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to show you is adding swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.01,0:27:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,actions to this application.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.24,0:27:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've decided that I'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.14,0:27:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,add the ability to favorite and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.22,0:28:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe delete some of these
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.13,0:28:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,things.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.66,0:28:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go to the memory view
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.31,0:28:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,controller and add support for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.35,0:28:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the new swipe actions in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.87,0:28:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it looks like a lot, but I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.26,0:28:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,walk you through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.92,0:28:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All I've done is implemented two
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.37,0:28:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,new methods; leading swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.30,0:28:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,actions configuration for road
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.74,0:28:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,indexpath and trailing swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.30,0:28:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,actions configurations for road
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.65,0:28:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,indexpath.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.96,0:28:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's walk through the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.65,0:28:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,leading one.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.93,0:28:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All I do is I create a UI
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.29,0:28:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,contextual action here, with a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.79,0:28:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,style of "normal," a title of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.27,0:28:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"favorite," and a block based
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.10,0:28:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.64,0:28:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I update our favorites state,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.26,0:28:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,using a method I wrote earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.54,0:28:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I call the completion
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.05,0:28:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,handler with the parameter of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.92,0:28:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"true."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.25,0:28:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just so everything's looking
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.33,0:28:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,right, I'll also set it to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.86,0:28:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"unfavorite," based on whether
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.25,0:28:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that item's already favorited.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.59,0:28:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll set the image to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.59,0:28:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,this beautiful star that I had
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,made earlier and the background
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.03,0:28:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,color to this awesome looking
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.36,0:28:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.44,0:28:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then all I need to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.11,0:28:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,create a UI swipe actions
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.30,0:28:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,configuration using that UI
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.22,0:29:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,contextual action and return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.39,0:29:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The story's pretty much the same
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.50,0:29:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for the trailing actions; I just
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.05,0:29:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,use the style of disruptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.38,0:29:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I recompile and rerun
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.92,0:29:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,this time, go back over, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.72,0:29:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,swipe, you'll notice we get this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.45,0:29:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,option swipe actions and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.61,0:29:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,even have a swipe action on the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.71,0:29:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,leading edge, as you see here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.98,0:29:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which you were never able to do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.16,0:29:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.84,0:29:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For full -- furthermore, you get
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.46,0:29:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,full swipe to delete support out
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.04,0:29:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.42,0:29:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So all I need to do is swipe all
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.17,0:29:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the way across and it just
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.60,0:29:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,works.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.52,0:29:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.17,0:29:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a look at some of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.44,0:29:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,new APIs for margins, insets,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.04,0:29:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll views, and bars in this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.00,0:29:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,demo app.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.70,0:29:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's looking really great and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.73,0:29:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,definitely ready for iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.48,0:29:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Kyle's going to come back up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.78,0:29:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell you about some related
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.73,0:29:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.52,0:29:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.37,0:29:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you again Raj.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.14,0:30:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So just to recap what we've
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.46,0:30:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,learned today; we've learned how
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.03,0:30:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to adopt large navigation titles
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.01,0:30:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the new integrated search
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.08,0:30:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,experience into our applications
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.81,0:30:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.01,0:30:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also learned about some
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.52,0:30:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,new improvements to layout
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.94,0:30:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,margins that give us complete
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.30,0:30:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,control over our views and the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.69,0:30:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,way they layout, as well as a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.62,0:30:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,new concept called the safe
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.83,0:30:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,area, which tells us about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.21,0:30:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,overlapping contents and things
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.01,0:30:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,like over scan compensation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.38,0:30:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,insets on Apple TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.00,0:30:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We've learned about some new
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.05,0:30:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements to UI scroll view
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.90,0:30:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that give us better control over
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.28,0:30:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,our content inset and some new
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.46,0:30:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,features in UI table view and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.29,0:30:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,how it interacts with concepts
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.78,0:30:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like the safe area.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.28,0:30:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have more questions be
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.10,0:30:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,sure to visit the site for this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.44,0:30:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.44,0:30:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a great WWDC.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.52,0:30:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
